				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Only if its changed to a 100% snare, and will work on unsnarable mobs the same way current root works on unrootable mobs.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
In my experience Earth Pet root doesn't land on unrootable mobs. Several times I've tried yoyo kiting mobs at C1 in Fire and Yxtta zone in and had root never land. Both of those types of mobs can rarely spawn as 'Immune to movement speed changes'.
<br />

<br />
I know for a fact that the root landed given I saw the spell message go off but the mob keeps running at you.
<br />

<br />
Similarly I've never seen Air/MS4 stun a mob flagged as unstunnable despite the fact the spell lands.
<br />

<br />
Also I think 100% snare would be massively open to abuse given the rate Earth pet casts its snare as the mob would be perma snared despite the 18sec duration (Earth pet would cast 3 times in 18secs, one is definitely going to land). You end up with a mob stood still 'chasing' you as the pet beats it down and is ignored as you chain nuke it, without it standing any chance of reaching you.
<br />

<br />
I think SOE have a good reason not to let any class have a 100% snare.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
Cestus Dei
<br />
Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
